[Attachment #2 (multipart/mixed)]


Updated patches for util-linux-2.12 have been posted to
<URL:http://www.stwing.org/~sluskyb/util-linux/>.

losetup and mount will now check cipher names and key sizes against
/proc/crypto, whether that's a file (ie. new CryptoAPI) or a directory
(old CryptoAPI). Thing is that it won't always work under the new
CryptoAPI: some ciphers (including AES and Twofish, possibly others)
require the key size to be a "round number" and may throw an EINVAL at you
even when the key size is between the listed minimum and maximum. Maybe
we ought to revive the keysize_mask from the old CryptoAPI?

I also created a combined patch (attached), which IMO is ready to be
included in util-linux. What do y'all think? (especially Andries)

--=20
